    <h1>Community Rules — StrangerTalk</h1>
    <p class="lead">Our goal is to keep StrangerTalk a safe and friendly place for everyone. By using the platform you agree to follow these rules.</p>

    <ol class="rules">
      <li><strong>Be Respectful:</strong> Treat every user with respect. No insults, harassment, threats, or abusive language.</li>
      <li><strong>No Hate Speech:</strong> Content that promotes hate, racism, sexism, or discrimination is strictly prohibited.</li>
      <li><strong>No Illegal Activities:</strong> Do not share, request, or discuss illegal content, instructions for wrongdoing, or any form of illicit activity.</li>
      <li><strong>No Adult or Explicit Content:</strong> Sharing sexually explicit, pornographic, or otherwise inappropriate adult content is forbidden.</li>
      <li><strong>Protect Personal Information:</strong> Do not share your or others’ personal information (phone numbers, addresses, passwords, ID numbers).</li>
      <li><strong>No Spamming or Advertising:</strong> Unsolicited promotions, repeated links, and mass-messaging are not allowed.</li>
      <li><strong>No Impersonation:</strong> Don’t pretend to be someone else, including platform staff, celebrities, or other users.</li>
      <li><strong>No Bots or Scripts:</strong> Automated tools, bots, or scripts that abuse the platform are banned.</li>
      <li><strong>Report Dangerous Behavior:</strong> If you see threats, self-harm content, or someone in immediate danger, report to us immediately.</li>
      <li><strong>Age Requirement:</strong> You must be 13+ to use StrangerTalk. Minors should not share personal contact details.</li>
      <li><strong>Account Responsibility:</strong> You are responsible for activity from your account—keep your login secure.</li>
      <li><strong>Enforcement:</strong> Violations may lead to warnings, temporary suspension, or permanent ban depending on severity.</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="note">
      <strong>Note:</strong> These rules are not exhaustive. We reserve the right to remove content and suspend accounts that harm the safety or integrity of the community.
    </div>

